> We can't get enough of the aromatic, richly-spiced flavors of Moroccan cuisine—so we're channeling them into a steamy, hearty stew that's sure to warm you from the inside out. Carrot, onion, and chickpeas are seasoned with garlic powder, earthy cumin, spicy chili flakes, fresh ginger, umami-packed tomato paste, and a smoky cinnamon paprika spice blend, then simmered in a tomato broth until thickened. It's all dolloped with lemony yogurt and served with garlicky toasted pitas for dipping, because you won't want to let a drop of this stew go to waste.

Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 400 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Trim, peel, and finely dice @carrot{3%ounce}(trimmed, peeled, and finely diced). Halve, peel, and finely dice half the @yellow onion{1%unit}(peeled and finely diced) (whole onion for 4 servings). Peel and mince @ginger{1%thumb}(peeled and minced). Drain @chickpeas{13.4%ounce}(drained) (no need to rinse). Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(roughly chopped).

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. (Use a #large pot{} for 4 servings.) Add carrot, diced onion, and a big pinch of @salt{pinch}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until just softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in ginger, @cumin{1%teaspoon}, @smoky cinnamon paprika spice{1%tablespoon}, half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest later), and a pinch of @?chili flakes{1%teaspoon} if desired. Cook, stirring, for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @tomato paste{1.5%ounce} and chickpeas. Cook, stirring, for ~{1%minute}.

Add @diced tomatoes{14%ounce}(undrained), @veggie stock concentrate{3%unit}, 1 1/2 cups warm @water{1.5%cups}, half the cilantro, @sugar{1/2%teaspoon}, @pepper{}(to taste), and a couple big pinches of @salt{pinch} to #pot{}. Bring to a boil, scraping up any browned bits from bottom of pot.

Reduce heat to medium low and simmer until thickened, ~{10-12%minutes}.

> The stew should be fairly thick—if you prefer it a bit brothier, add water 1 TBSP at a time until it reaches desired consistency.

While stew simmers, zest and quarter @lemon{1%unit}(zested and quartered).

In a #small bowl{}, combine @yogurt{2%tablespoon}, a squeeze of lemon juice, and a pinch of lemon zest. Season with @salt{}(to taste).

Place @whole wheat pitas{2%unit} on a #baking sheet{}; brush or drizzle with @olive oil{2%teaspoon}. Sprinkle with remaining garlic powder and salt.

Toast on middle rack of oven until golden, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Stir a squeeze of lemon juice and a pinch of remaining lemon zest into stew. Taste and season with salt, pepper, and more lemon juice and zest if desired.

Divide stew between #bowls{} and top with lemony yogurt and remaining cilantro. Serve garlic pitas on the side.

> Tear off and dip in pieces while you eat! Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.